text: Hollensville is an unincorporated community in Audrain County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== A post office was established at Hollensville in 1896, and remained in operation until 1907. J. W. Hollingshead, an early postmaster, gave the community his last name. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Audrain County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Hollensville, Missouri
